'''Robert Stieglitz''' (born June 20, 1981 in [[Yeysk]], [[Russia]] as ''Sergey Shtikhlits'') is a [[Germany|German]] professional [[Boxing|boxer]] and the current [[World Boxing Organization|WBO]] [[Super Middleweight]] Champion. Stieglitz resides in [[Magdeburg]], [[Sachsen-Anhalt]], Germany.

== Professional career ==
Robert suffered his second loss to [[Mexico]]'s [[Librado Andrade]] in eight rounds at the Morongo Casino Resort & Spa, Cabazon, California in an [[International Boxing Federation|IBF]] [[Super Middleweight]] Title Eliminator.<ref>http://www.boxingforecast.com/blog/index.cfm?commentID=263</ref> Stieglitz won the vacant WBC International Super Middleweight title on December 9, 2008 in [[Sölden]] ([[Austria]]) to previously unbeaten [[Lukas Wilaschek]].

=== WBO Super Middleweight Champion ===
Stieglitz vacated the [[World Boxing Council|WBC]] International belt June 22, 2009 to fight [[Karoly Balzsay]] for the [[World Boxing Organization|WBO]] Super Middleweight title. At the end of round ten, as a groggy and beaten Balzsay barely wobbled back to his corner, Balzsay's trainer Fritz Sdinek called for help and Balzsay was quickly taken from the ring to the hospital on a stretcher with his neck in a neck brace.<ref>http://www.eastsideboxing.com/news.php?p=20912&more=1</ref> Stieglitz recorded a fifth-round technical knockout of [[Ruben Eduardo Acosta]] to retain his WBO Super Middleweight title. The fight was stopped at 1:48 to give Stieglitz the victory in his first defense.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tsn.ca/boxing/story/?id=305438|title=Stieglitz Stops Acosta To Retain WBO Super Middleweight Belt|date=9 January 2010|publisher=[[The Sports Network|TSN]]|accessdate=11 March 2010}}</ref> On April 17, 2010 he successfully defended his title in Magdeburg against Eduard Gutknecht.<ref>http://www.boxingscene.com/zbik-decisions-spada-again-stieglitz-beats-gutknecht--26999</ref>

Stieglitz retained his title with a hard-fought unanimous decision over his [[Mexico|Mexican]] challenger [[Enrique Ornelas]], Andrade's younger brother, at the Freiberger Arena in Dresden. It was a slow start of both fights and little less action but Stieglitz started this fight in style in the second round. The German champion progressed the fight with his sharp jab to give Ornelas some trouble but the Mexican also landed some precise and dangerous shots towards Stieglitz.<ref>http://www.boxingscene.com/robert-stieglitz-decisions-enrique-ornelas-tough-war--33035</ref>

He would then make successful defenses against [[Khoren Gevor]] and Henry Weber. <ref>http://www.boxingscene.com/robert-stieglitz-beats-khoren-gevor-by-dq-ten-rounds--37947</ref><ref>http://www.boxingscene.com/robert-stieglitz-punishes-weber-mikkel-kessler-next--48535</ref> Stieglitz was supposed to face former three-time titleholder [[Mikkel Kessler]] in his hometown of [[Copenhagen, Denmark]] to defend his 168-pound belt on April 14, 2012<ref>http://espn.go.com/boxing/story/_/id/6869219/supper-middleweight-robert-stieglitz-take-mikkel-kessler</ref> but Kessler pulled out due to injury. Instead, he defended the title with a unanimous decision win over Nader Hamdan on May 5, 2012.<ref>http://www.boxingscene.com/huck-afolabi-battle-draw-pulev-stieglitz-win--52558</ref>

Stieglitz would then lose the WBO Super Middleweight Championship to [[Arthur Abraham]] on August 25, 2013.<ref>http://www.boxingscene.com/arthur-abraham-decisions-stieglitz-captures-wbo-crown--56391</ref> He would rebound with a win over Michal Nieroda on January 26, 2013 before avenging his loss to Abraham and regaining the WBO Super Middleweight Championship with a fourth-round knockout on March 23, 2013.<ref>http://www.boxingscene.com/stieglitz-restores-career-by-taking-king-arthurs-crown--63687</ref>

His first defense in his second reign as WBO Super Middleweight Champion was a tenth-round TKO win over Yuzo Kiyota on July 13, 2013.<ref>http://www.boxingscene.com/robert-steiglitz-retains-beats-yuzo-kiyota-ten--67622</ref> The result was originally announced as a Techinal Decision win for Stieglitz, but was changed to a TKO after the Bund Deutscher Berufsboxer examined the ending of the fight and concluded that Stieglitz did not accidentally headbutt Kiyota. The change was approved by the WBO.<ref>http://www.boxingscene.com/stieglitzs-victory-over-kiyota-changed-tko-win--67906</ref>

